notes: invariable numeral; combines in compounds like duecentouno
used as a numeral noun; invariable form
used when referring to a two-hundred-euro bill
example_sentence_italian: Ho trovato un duecento per terra.
example_sentence_english: I found a two-hundred-euro bill on the ground.

notes: used to refer to the denomination, the year, or the century
example_sentence_italian: Il duecento è spesso studiato in storia.
example_sentence_english: The thirteenth century is often studied in history.

notes: plural uses the same form; invariable
example_sentence_italian: Duecento erano in fila davanti alla porta.
example_sentence_english: Two hundred were in line in front of the door.
I duecento hanno firmato il documento.
column24: The two hundred signed the document.

notes: partitive plural form; rare but possible in colloquial contexts
